rows.name: Ask Horonalderon about recent developments.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079301_MSG0001
rows.name:
Even when we were in the Ganglion,
we heard rumors of her cruelty. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079301_MSG0002
rows.name:
*fsssh* They say she tortures prisoners of war to death,
and also slaughters native peoples without orders just
to see the torment on their faces.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079301_MSG0003
rows.name:
I've seen even the cruelest of Ganglion soldiers look
repulsed upon learning that they've being transferred
into her unit. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079301_MSG0004
rows.name:
That said, I've also seen some request to join her forces
just so they could unleash their unbridled bloodlust as
savage Prone do. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079301_MSG0009
rows.name:
You could say that we are engaged in a search-and-
recovery mission just like you BLADEs. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079301_MSG0010
rows.name:
The difference is that while you're seeking pieces of
your Lifehold, we're searching for the toxic materials
called voltant that are concealed within New LA. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079301_MSG0011
rows.name:
We know that voltant can be found throughout Mira
as well, and we must find and purify it all. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079301_MSG0012
rows.name:
That is our nature as Zaruboggan, and our calling.
Either way, it is a duty we cannot ignore. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079301_MSG0013
rows.name:
Though there exist exceptions, like my subordinate
Phoskeran, who are not faithful to that duty. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079301_MSG0018
rows.name:
It appears that you humans have managed to expand
your sphere of influence to encompass Sylvalum and
Cauldros as well. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079301_MSG0019
rows.name:
I've heard that rare metals like infernium, parhelion
platinum, and cimmerian cinnabar can be mined
there. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079301_MSG0020
rows.name:
I only hope that your exploration teams can stay ahead
of the Ganglion's. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079301_MSG0021
rows.name:
If they do—and if you have the extra room—it would
be most appreciated if you could bring some of the
voltant-rich ores back to New LA. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079301_MSG0022
rows.name:
I, along with my brethren, would be happy to take
responsibility for devoltanizing them. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079301_MSG1001
rows.name:
Thanks to you and Piers, everything concluded safely.
My deepest gratitude to you! *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079301_MSG1002
rows.name:
But as for Phoskeran, I never imagined that his
incompetence ran so deep. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079301_MSG1003
rows.name:
If only your mimeosomes were able to resist voltant,
I'd ask you humans to take over his job. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079301_MSG1004
rows.name:
Er, would that be too dangerous? *fsssh*
If you're interested, please let me know![ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079301_MSG2001
rows.name:
Thanks to you and Piers, everything concluded safely.
My deepest gratitude to you! *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079301_MSG2002
rows.name:
And as for Phoskeran... Well, I never imagined he'd
rise to the occasion in a time of crisis. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079301_MSG2003
rows.name:
Frankly, I'd always thought he was a complete fool,
but it seems I may have been mistaken. *fsssh*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079301_MSG2004
rows.name: Perhaps it's time I gave him a more important job...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: tev079301_MSG2005
rows.name:
Does that scare you? Don't worry! *fsssh*
Knowing him, I'm sure he'll excavate some voltant that
no one else would have been able to find.[ST:wait ]
